From: Matthew Feickert <matthew.feickert@cern.ch>
Date: Thu, 16 Apr 2026 00:40:19 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] fix: Add CMake install target

* Add install target for Python to place the dynamically linked HIP library
  in the correct site-packages directory.
   - c.f. https://cmake.org/cmake/help/latest/module/FindPython.html
---
 src/c/Python/CMakeLists.txt | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/src/c/Python/CMakeLists.txt b/src/c/Python/CMakeLists.txt
index 8c86a71..a1e8043 100644
--- a/src/c/Python/CMakeLists.txt
+++ b/src/c/Python/CMakeLists.txt
@@ -96,3 +96,5 @@ target_sources(HydraPy
         HydraPyModule.cpp
         PyCommandModule.cpp
 )
+
+install(TARGETS HydraPy LIBRARY DESTINATION "${Python_SITEARCH}")
